attempted takeover of two companies in order to avoid a long drawn 
out legal battle with the government 
the payment settles a suit filed by the federal trade commission 
over his 1986 stock purchases in holiday corp and bally 
manufacturing corp 
both cases involved the purchase of stock options through bear 
stearns amp co which in turn bought actual shares the ftc 
contends the exercise of stock options was covered by rules 
requiring that buyers notify the government before purchasing more 
than 15 million worth of voting stock in a company and wait 30 
days before completing the transaction 
trump said tuesday he was advised by his lawyers and the 
investment firm that stock options were exempt and he should be 
reimbursed by bear stearns a bear stearns spokeswoman had no 
immediate comment 
