bill thomas will retire in 1989 after 18 splendid years as 
editor this announcement is being made now to provide for an 
orderly transition johnson said monday 
coffey joined the washington post in 1968 as a sports writer and 
subsequently became editor of the posts magazine editor of its 
style section deputy managing editor and assistant managing editor 
for national news 
he became editor of us news amp world report in 1985 and editor 
of the dallas times herald in 1986 before joining the times that 
year 
