<TEXT>
us military guards today reclaimed 27 
remains believed to be those of americans killed in the vietnam war 
the largest such repatriation since 1973 
the us military team saluted as the remains each in a metal 
case topped with a folded american flag were loaded one by one 
onto a us air force cargo plane for a flight to army laboratories 
in hawaii the brief solemn ceremony was held under overcast skies 
