former us sen paul laxalt says an award 
of nearly 650000 in legal costs makes him the victor in a more 
than fouryear libel battle against mcclatchy newspapers 
the public knows well that winners arent ordered to fork over 
hundreds of thousands of dollars and no amount of distortion by 
the bee newspaper regarding todays decision will dispel that 
basic fact laxalt said in a statement issued in washington 
this should prove that it is not impossible for a public 
servant to win the good fight against a wealthy and powerful 
newspaper chain 
the award announced monday marks the end of a protracted legal 
battle that began in november 1983 when the bee newspapers in 
sacramento modesto and fresno published an article about the 
family of laxalt a longtime confidante of president reagan and 
then a republican senator from nevada 
the article alleged that the internal revenue service had 
evidence of skimming at the ormsby house hotelcasino in carson 
city nev while the laxalt family owned it in the early 1970s 
the action was dropped in june 1987 and the two sides then 
entered arbitration over fees with laxalts side requesting 
approximately 43 million in fees and costs the threemember 
panel griffin b bell charles b renfrew and philip w tone 
entered their award last thursday for 647454 in fees and costs 
which will be paid by mcclatchys insurance carrier 
the award also provides that 130363 in fees and expenses for 
the arbitrators will be shared by both parties 
mcclatchy newspapers said in a statement it would have preferred 
its insurance company not pay any of the fees but called the award 
fair to all parties 
we are pleased that this long legal battle is finally over 
but lets hope its lessons are not forgotten the publishing 
company said in a statement the first amendment is meaningless 
without a strong independent and vigilant press willing to stand 
up for its beliefs 
its a hell of a victory said attorney james beasley who 
represented laxalt thats over half a million in counsel fees 
that laxalt doesnt have to pay you only pay counsel fees to the 
winner 
the laxalt libel defense fund already has paid 680000 in legal 
fees related to the case according to laxalts daughter michelle 
who runs a political consulting firm in washington dc mcclatchy 
newspapers is not required to pay reimbursement for those costs 
