<TEXT>
state authorities announced wednesday 
they will make public most of files of the los angeles police 
departments investigation of the 1968 assassination of robert f 
kennedy including the departments final uncensored investigative 
report 
the huge file to be made public april 19 have been stored in 
the state archives since last august and include some 2500 
photographs 50000 square feet of written material and interviews 
with 4000 witnesses 
most of the material has been sealed since 1969 although a 
partial summary of the files was released in 1986 
secretary of state march fong eu whose office has custody of 
the files said officials will release all materials except those 
prohibited by specific laws and those which fall within another law 
enforcement agencys jurisdiction the withheld material includes 
autopsy photos juvenile records and fingerprint cards 
most of the documents to be released have never before been made 
public eu said she added that much of the manuscript material is 
fragile and faded and of an irreplaceable nature 
kennedy was shot june 5 1968 in the ambassador hotel moments 
after claiming victory in the california democratic presidential 
primary he died the following day 
sirhan bishara sirhan a native of jordan was convicted of the 
killing and sentenced to die in the san quentin gas chamber but 
his death sentence was changed to life imprisonment in 1972 when 
the california supreme court outlawed the death penalty 
he is currently imprisoned at soledad where he has since been 
denied parole numerous times since he first became eligible to 
apply for parole in 1975 
the lapd investigation into the robert f kennedy 
assassination by sirhan sirhan was exhaustive yet public concern 
about its conclusions remains 20 years later eu said in a 
written statement released by her office in light of that 
concern we believe the publics right know generally outweighs 
privacy concerns and have governed our public release of these 
materials with that guideline 
the files include reports of investigations of specific 
conspiracy theories sirhan has since said he acted alone in 
killing kennedy and audio and video tapes from the crime scene 
the material has been stored in sacramento since last august 
under an agreement between los angeles and the state the agreement 
followed a lengthy effort by scholars and other interested persons 
to persuade los angeles police officials not to keep the material 
secret 
</TEXT>
