<TEXT>
the hijackers of a kuwait airlines jet 
released 32 more passengers in iran early thursday but warned that 
those remaining would be in danger if authorities failed to meet 
the hijackers demands irans official news agency reported 
the release left about 50 passengers and crew members aboard the 
plane 
the hijackers warned in a statement that three members of the 
kuwaiti royal family who are still aboard the aircraft would pay a 
dear price if the conditions were not fulfilled the agency 
reported 
the release of the 32 additional passengers came a day after the 
hijackers freed 25 hostages one ailing man and 24 women 
the gunmen are demanding the release of 17 shiite moslems 
convicted and imprisoned in kuwait for bombing the us and french 
embassies in 1983 
deputy prime minister ali reza moayyeri told iranian television 
wednesday that talks on the emergency were under way between 
kuwaiti foreign ministry officials who flew to iran and officials 
of the tehran government 
the kidnappers however accused the kuwaiti delegation of 
wasting its time and asked the iranians to mediate between the 
hijackers and kuwaitis reported irans islamic republic news 
agency or irna 
in their statement the hijackers also warned iranian security 
forces not to take any action against the plane and the hijackers 
irna reported 
the agency quoted the hijackers as saying in a statement that 
they wanted the world to realize the real nature of the kuwaiti 
rulers who have overlooked all the problems of the muslim world at 
the top of them the issue of palestine and the brave palestinians 
who are fighting israel 
the hijackers said they would free any hostage they thought had 
nothing to do with the issues involved irna reported but keep the 
others and treat them in such a way as to settle our account 
with kuwait 
in a conversation with the airport control tower later the 
hijackers said they were considering releasing all nonkuwaiti 
passengers the agency said 
thirty kuwaitis were on the passenger list 
irna said the 32 people released at 230 am thursday 7 pm 
wednesday edt included two crew members a sudanese and a 
yemenite all those freed were brought to the transit lounge of 
mashhad airport and were under medical care it added 
it added that immediately after the release the hijackers closed 
the doors and switched off the lights in the aircraft cabin 
the hijackers earlier insisted that the boeing 747 be refueled 
tehran radio quoted airport authorities at mashhad in northeastern 
iran as saying they would refuel the plane to prevent any 
calamity or incident 
food was brought wednesday to those still aboard the jet 
irna quoted a freed jordanian passenger as saying there were 
five or six hijackers who wore masks and were armed with pistols 
and hand grenades 
there originally were 112 people on the plane 
crown prince sheik saad alabdullah alsabah presided at an 
emergency meeting of the kuwaiti cabinet on tuesday night and said 
the government would not submit to blackmail 
relatives have identified the royal prisoners as two sisters in 
their early 30s ebtesam khaled alsabah and anware khaled 
alsabah and brother fadel khaled alsabah described as a 
businessman in his 40s 
in washington the state department praised the sheikdom for 
refusing to yield declaring kuwait has taken an exemplary 
position in the struggle against international terrorism and we 
applaud them for it 
twelve britons were on the plane before the release early 
thursday prime minister margaret thatcher said she would not ask 
kuwait to negotiate and told reporters we do not give in to 
blackmail because it only leads to further tragedies 
in tehran senior military spokesman kamal kharrazi told a news 
conference attended by an associated press reporter the 
hijackers identity is still not known to us we only know that 
they speak arabic and want the prisoners in kuwait to be freed 
five flight attendants among the women released wednesday said a 
masked man brandishing a pistol announced the hijack in english as 
the plane flew over india on tuesday 
a physician identified only as dr qassem was sent to the 
aircraft wednesday at the request of the hijackers irna quoted him 
as saying he treated two arabicspeaking women and the condition 
of one was not satisfactory 
a passenger list released in bangkok where flight 422 
originated indicated the only two women left on the plane were the 
members of the royal family 
the hijackers freed 24 women early wednesday after 20 hours in 
captivity and jordanian businessman mustafa issa 42 who suffers 
from a heart condition was released tuesday irna reported 
release of the 17 jailed shiites has been a recurring demand of 
shiite fundamentalist groups loyal to iranian ayatollah ruhollah 
khomeini that are believed to hold most of the 22 western hostages 
in lebanon 
many acts of terrorism in kuwait have been blamed on shiite 
moslems acting for iran which has been at war with iraq since 
september 1980 and accuses the sheikdom of being its enemys ally 
no precise list of the nationalities of the remaining hostages 
was available because of differences in lists released by irna and 
the airline 
