<DOCNO> AP880406-0223 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
internal revenue service form 4868 is surely a 
popular piece of paper right now 
for those who have not yet had occasion to use it 4868 is the 
document taxpayers must file by april 15 to get an automatic 
extension of the deadline on their federal tax returns 
such extensions are in heavy demand this year with taxpayers 
and paid preparers struggling to adjust to the new system that went 
into effect in 1987 mandated by tax reform 
confusion has been running high about many provisions of the new 
code even among professional veterans of the tax wars 
suppose for example that you have passive losses from some 
partnership activity the irs recently released 265 pages of 
temporary passive loss regulations and this is only the 
beginning observed the jk lasser tax institute in its current 
monthly bulletin 
if you are overwhelmed by tax questions preoccupied by other 
pressing matters or simply in a mood to procrastinate you can put 
off the deadline for completing your return until aug 15 by simply 
filing form 4868 now 
for this extension unlike any subsequent one you might seek 
the government doesnt require any explanation or excuse but if 
uncle sam has any money coming from you he wants it now not later 
the rules require that you include with form 4868 a check for 
the estimated balance of what you still owe beyond what was 
withheld from your wages or salary and any other payments you have 
already made 
the estimate should be made with some care if it turns out that 
you still owe money for 1987 when you file your return on say 
june 30 the government will charge you interest at a 10 percent 
annual rate on the balance due 
and if what you still owe amounts to more than 10 percent of 
your total tax bill for the year a penalty may also be imposed 
although it is a helpful option to have an extension is not 
always an unmixed blessing 
for one thing if you have a refund coming you cant claim it 
with form 4868 that has to wait until your return is filed and in 
the interim the government has what amounts to the free use of the 
money 
that cost may be a small one to pay however if an extension 
allows you or your professional preparer the breathing space 
necessary to make a careful computation of every tax break to which 
you are entitled 
extensions are also automatically granted without a form 4868 
for two months if you can document that you were out of the united 
states or puerto rico on april 15 but a quick dash across the 
border and back will no longer do the trick 
nettled by an airlines advertisements touting foreign travel as 
a tax dodge the irs recently said these extensions apply only to 
people who can show that they were out of the country for at least 
14 consecutive days including all of april 15 
does an extension in any form increase or reduce your chances 
of getting audited probably not says the arthur young tax guide 
some tax experts contend that you should request the maximum 
extension allowed for filing your return arguing that the chances 
of an audit are reduced since irs field agents will have less time 
to conduct the audit the accounting firm says 
other tax experts contend youre better off filing on april 15 
since this way you get lost in the crowd both theories are 
oversimplifications of irs procedures 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

