the 1988 pontiac bonneville sse is more than a 
technology buffs dream come true 
its an impressive road car and comfortable large sedan that 
even a technophobe can appreciate 
inside the aerodynamically styled vehicle a driver can tune the 
radio without taking his hands off the steering wheel the radio 
buttons are built into the wheel around the horn an electronic 
compass senses the earths magnetic field thus changes in the 
sses direction are continuously displayed on an electronic map on 
the dashboard 
and a new smooth fuelinjected 3800 v6 wonderfully firm 
suspension goodyear eagle gt4 radial tires and antilock brakes 
join to provide stable road handling and enjoyable ride 
yes the sse is a car to show off to friends and neighbors but 
it doesnt come cheaply base price is 21879 
you get what you pay for the sse is so loaded with standard 
equipment there are only three options alarm system interior 
leather and power sunroof 
additionally the sse is priced below many of its foreign 
