<TEXT>
reed funks grass has shimmered in the rose 
bowl in yankee stadium on the masters golf course and across 
thousands of private lawns 
hes got a famous touch with turf but the 59yearold 
researcher and academician says the grass is always greener 
somewhere else 
you start out with a variety and then immediately start 
working on a replacement thats better because nothing is 
perfect he said 
colleagues and others involved in the turf industry say funk has 
taken an unknown field and made it his own revolutionizing the 
development of grass and gaining international prominence in the 
process 
a rutgers university researcher and turf science professor funk 
has been developing scores of grass varieties for more than 20 
years in his new brunswick offices and on 200 acres of test fields 
in adelphia funk combines various strains of grass seed in search 
of the best combination 
funk has created finetextured turf grasses lush dark green 
grasses shade and droughttolerant grasses and grasses that repel 
disease and insects bearing such names as rebel gator and prelude 
he is often referred to as the albert einstein of the seed 
