w russell boss a former president 
and chairman of penmaker at cross co has died at age 79 
boss died monday at holy cross hospital in fort lauderdale 
boss began working as sales manager and treasurer of cross in 
1937 shortly after the death of his father walter russell boss 
sr owner of the rhode islandbased company 
over the next 27 years boss rose to become chairman and 
president of the company and helped it evolve from a private 
familyowned business with a dozen employees to a public company 
with 1554 million in revenue and more than 1400 employees 
worldwide 
boss in 1979 relinquished the chairmanship he had held since 
1971 to his eldest son bradford r boss of barrington ri he 
remained vice chairman until 1985 when he was named chairman 
emeritus 
the providence ri native served on the american automobile 
associations governing board and bred thoroughbred horses in 
florida 
boss was survived by his wife doris two sons a sister and six 
grandchidren 
services were scheduled for saturday in cranston ri 
