despite a slight drop in the european 
economic communitys economic sentiment indicator in february the 
12nation trading bloc is not heading for a recession the eec 
reported wednesday 
the eec commission citing the latest business and consumer 
survey said there were no signs of an approaching recession 
it said the stock market crash and the turbulence on 
foreignexchange markets last fall affected economic performance 
less than originally feared 
the commission said the eecs economic indicator which is based 
partly on the results of the survey dropped to 1027 in february 
from 1029 in january but was above the 1026 level recorded in 
november 1987 after the october crash 
the indicator comprises an industrial confidence indicator a 
construction confidence indicator a consumer confidence indicator 
and stock price indexes 
eec economists reported that production expectations continued 
to point toward further growth over the next few months while the 
outlook for exports looked brighter than anticipated 
lowerthanexpected production results in britain since last 
december have led industrialists there to revise their production 
expectations significantly downward the commission said 
the consumer confidence indicator lost a point in february over 
