<TEXT>
top officials of the trades union congress met 
wednesday to consider what the organizations policy should be 
regarding controversial singleunion and nostrike deals issues 
which threaten to split up the tuc 
two member unions which have reached such deals on their own 
have threatened to pull out of the tuc britains umbrella labor 
union organization over the issue 
the tucs special review body made up of about 20 members of 
its general council held a oneday meeting to consider various 
proposals the review body includes the tucs general secretary 
norman willis 
the issue is whether or not there should be some form of 
direction to unions about singleunion and nostrike deals and if 
there were such things how they should be sanctioned said a tuc 
spokesman who spoke on condition he not be identified by name 
i am not aware of any particular details he said 
the review body was formed at the tucs annual convention last 
september to review several areas it is considering among other 
things whether unions should be required to ballot their members 
before agreeing to such deals the times of london reported 
the body which has been holding a series of meetings is 
expected to announce its recommendations in a report issued before 
the next convention in september at which tuc delegates would vote 
on them 
britains unions have been bitterly divided over whether to 
accept these deals which have become more common in recent years 
particularly at plants owned by japanese companies 
the unions have disagreed on how best to fight the loss of their 
power under the conservative government of prime minister margaret 
thatcher which has introduced unioncurbing legislation that for 
example requires unions to ballot their members before calling a 
strike 
the deals are strongly opposed by ron todd head of the 
transport and general workers union britains largest union 
eric hammond general secretary of the electricians union known 
as the eetpu has threatened several times to ballot his 336000 
members on pulling out of the tuc 
hammond has the support of bill jordan president of the 
amalgamated engineering union who also has warned that he would 
try to bring his 857000strong union out of the tuc if he were 
prevented from signing more of the controversial deals 
the aeu is the countrys secondlargest union 
