expectations that the fed would tighten its policy and raise 
interest rates had been depressing stock market psychology he said 
larry wachtel a market watcher for prudentialbache securities 
inc said the dollars strength soon rippled through the bond 
market sending longterm rates lower that in turn made yields on 
stocks look more attractive he said 
in each of the markets he said traders who had sold borrowed 
contracts in expectations that the dollar bonds and stocks would 
fall suddenly saw prices rising and felt compelled to buy in an 
effort to cut their potential losses 
too many people were selling the market short he said 
the voluntary restrictions on program trading were called into 
play after the dow jones average passed the 50point gain mark at 
about 319 pm edt a spokeswoman for the exchange said 
program trading a technique used by brokerages to profit on 
price differences between stocks and the corresponding stockindex 
futures has been blamed for injecting volatility into the market 
and frightening investors 
among activelytraded issues on the nyse american telephone amp 
telegraph rose 1 to 28 texaco rose 1 to 49 exxon climbed 2 to 
44 and general electric rose 1 to 41 
fw woolworth fell 1 to 54 the stock shot up more than 11 a 
share in the previous two sessions after a group led by dart group 
corp chairman herbert haft expressed interest in acquiring a stake 
in the retailer 
elsewhere in the retail group sears rose 1 to 37 k mart 
climbed 1 to 35 and jc penney rose 1 to 48 
the automakers rolled up some impressive advances after 
reporting strong latemarch sales general motors rose 3 to 74 
ford jumped 1 to 46 and chrysler rose 1 to 24 
as measured by wilshire associates index of more than 5000 
actively traded stocks the market gained 5565 billion or 216 
percent in value 
nationwide turnover in nyselisted issues including trades in 
those stocks on regional exchanges and in the overthecounter 
market totaled 22598 million shares 
